The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 16 injured in twin mishaps
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       16 injured in twin mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Sixteen people were injured in two mishaps on Wednesday. Three vehicles were impounded. The condition of the injured was stable.        
	Ten persons were injured when a private bus on route 3C/1 hit a stationary bus on route 46A at Esplanade around 3.30pm.         
	Six persons sitting in the rear of the 46A bus and four on the other bus were injured. They were taken to Medical College and Hospital, said Vineet Goyel, the deputy commissioner of police, headquarters.        
	A preliminary probe revealed that the driver of the 3C/1 bus lost control after the brakes failed. The bus has been impounded for fitness test. The other bus, too, was taken to Hare Street police station.        
	In the other mishap, six people were injured when a lorry rammed into a roadside shanty, near the crossing of the EM Bypass and Beleghata Main Road.        
	The lorry was heading towards Chingrihata. The driver lost control after overtaking a bus and mounted the pavement. On seeing the lorry, residents tried to run away. Six of them were injured after being hit by the vehicle. They have been admitted to NRS Hospital. The lorry has been impounded, said an officer of the traffic department at Lalbazar.        
